*CSS animation(transform, transition) don't work with display property.


*animate modal: Following will bring the modal from above from fading and again send above while fading out on close of modal
.modal{
	//other styles
	transition: all 0.3s ease-out; 
}
this says whenever any property changes, animate .modal in 0.3 seconds with ease-out transition, below properties are changing
conditionally that's when animation will be applied

.modal-open{
	opacity: 1;
	transform: translateY(0);//this will bring modal from 0 of the Y-axis
}
.modal-close{
	opacity: 0;
	transform: translateY(-100%); //this will send modal up while closing
}

this is a nice way but limits the animation, if above is our usecase then it will work find


*if we want some more flexibility in animation, we have more control on animation, then we can use the following:
In following we will get our modal from top but it will go little bit lower than our mid point and then animate back to mid point
It will bounce back to desired position

.modal{
	//other styling
	transition: all 0.3s ease-out;
}

.modal-open{
	animation: openModal 0.4s ease-out forwards; 
}
//forwards will make make our modal stay to the final styling, otherwise modal will go back to initial state
.modal-close{
	animation: closeModal 0.4s ease-out forwards;
}

@keyframes openModal {
    0% {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(-100%); //this will make modal to come from above of the page on Y-axis
    }//this tells how our modal should be in starting state while opening
    50% {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(90%); //this will make our modal go more down than the middle
    }//this tells how our modal should be in middle of opening
    100% {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0); //this will make modal to again come up to the middle
    }//this tells how our modal should be in end after opening
}

@keyframes closeModal {
    0% {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
    }
    50% {
        opacity: 0.8;
        transform: translateY(60%);
    }
    100% {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(-100%);
    }
}


*for rotating the element (I'm not sure what media query is used for in the following)

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
  .App-logo {
    animation: App-logo-spin infinite 20s linear;
  }
}

@keyframes App-logo-spin {
  from {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
  to {
    transform: rotate(360deg);
  }
}


